UsageSetting Up GitHub: Create an account on GitHub if you don't have one. 
- You can follow this link : https://docs.github.com/en/get-started/start-your-journey/creating-an-account-on-github

 Go to GitHub:
->Open your web browser and go to GitHub.
 Sign Up for an Account:
-> On the GitHub homepage, click the "Sign up" button in the top right corner.
Enter Your Information:
->Username: Choose a unique username that you will use to log in and identify yourself on GitHub.
->Email Address: Enter a valid email address that you have access to. This will be used for account verification and notifications.
->Password: Choose a strong password. Make sure itâ€™s something secure that you can remember.
 Verify Your Account:
->GitHub will ask you to verify that you are not a robot. Complete the CAPTCHA challenge as prompted.
Choose Your Plan:
->GitHub offers free and paid plans. For most users, the free plan is sufficient to get started.
->Select the plan that best suits your needs. For now, you can select the "Free" plan.
Personalize Your Experience:
->GitHub will ask you a few questions to personalize your experience. You can choose your level of experience with coding and your interest in using GitHub. This helps GitHub provide more relevant information and tips.
Verify Your Email Address:
->GitHub will send a verification email to the email address you provided. Check your email inbox and click on the verification link in the email to verify your email address.
Complete Your Profile (Optional):
-> After verifying your email, you can complete your profile by adding a profile picture, bio, and other optional details. This helps others know more about you when they visit your profile

Explain the steps you took to set up your GitHub account. 
- I followed the same steps given. 
- Follow this link - https://docs.github.com/en/get-started/onboarding/getting-started-with-your-github-account
